Handwriting Practice
Did you know?

The average person blinks about 15-20 
times per minute or about 20,000 times
per day. Blinking helps to moisten and
protect the surface of the eye by spreading
tears over the cornea. It also helps to clear
debris and foreign particles from the eye.

The human body has about 600 to 700
muscles. The number of muscles an
individual has can vary due to factors
such as age, gender, and overall health.

These muscles are responsible for various
functions such as movement, posture, and
facial expressions.
